    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1866-03-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1866-03-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="48" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d48">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Romero</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1866-03-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">March</hi> 14, 1866.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your note of the 31st of January last, requesting information
                            respecting the reported capture of the town of Bagdad, on the Rio
                            Bravo.</p>
                <p>In reply, I have to state that no official information upon the subject
                            has been received at this department.</p>
                <p>I avail myself of this occasion to renew to you, sir, the assurances of
                            my distinguished consideration.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Señor <hi rend="smallcaps">Matias Romero</hi>, <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
